    {
      "content": "The User Portal is an IIS web site which allows users to enroll in Azure Multi-Factor Authentication and maintain their accounts.",
      "pos": [
        788,
        917
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A user may change their phone number, change their PIN, or bypass Azure Multi-Factor Authentication during their next sign on.",
      "pos": [
        918,
        1044
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Users will log in to the User Portal using their normal username and password and will either complete a Azure Multi-Factor Authentication call or answer security questions to complete their authentication.",
      "pos": [
        1047,
        1253
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If user enrollment is allowed, a user will configure their phone number and PIN the first time they log in to the User Portal.",
      "pos": [
        1254,
        1380
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "User Portal Administrators may be set up and granted permission to add new users and update existing users.",
      "pos": [
